## Terraform Module Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[terraform/main.tf] --> B[modules/vpc]
    A --> C[modules/security]
    A --> D[modules/ecr]
    A --> E[modules/rds]
    A --> F[modules/ec2]
    
    B -- vpc_id --> C
    B -- private_subnet_ids --> E
    B -- public_subnet_ids --> F
    C -- rds_sg_id --> E
    C -- ec2_sg_id --> F
    D -- ecr_urls --> F
    E -- rds_endpoint --> F
```

## AWS Resources Created by Terraform

| Resource | Type | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| VPC | `aws_vpc` | Isolated network (10.0.0.0/16) |
| Public Subnet 1 | `aws_subnet` | EC2 lives here (10.0.1.0/24) |
| Public Subnet 2 | `aws_subnet` | High availability (10.0.2.0/24) |
| Private Subnet 1 | `aws_subnet` | RDS lives here (10.0.10.0/24) |
| Private Subnet 2 | `aws_subnet` | RDS failover (10.0.11.0/24) |
| Internet Gateway | `aws_internet_gateway` | Public internet access |
| Route Table | `aws_route_table` | Routes public traffic to IGW |
| EC2 Security Group | `aws_security_group` | SSH + ports 80, 3000, 8080 |
| RDS Security Group | `aws_security_group` | MySQL 3306 (from EC2 only) |
| ECR Backend | `aws_ecr_repository` | Docker image for Spring Boot |
| ECR Frontend | `aws_ecr_repository` | Docker image for React/Nginx |
| RDS MySQL | `aws_db_instance` | Managed MySQL database |
| EC2 Instance | `aws_instance` | App server running Docker |
| IAM Role | `aws_iam_role` | EC2 → ECR access |
| Instance Profile | `aws_iam_instance_profile` | Attaches IAM role to EC2 |

## Jenkins Pipeline Stages

```
Stage 1: Checkout      → Pull code from GitHub
Stage 2: AWS Setup     → Get AWS Account ID
Stage 3: Terraform     → terraform init/plan/apply
Stage 4: Build         → mvn package + npm build (parallel)
Stage 5: Docker Push   → Build & push images to ECR
Stage 6: Deploy to EC2 → SSH in, pull images, restart containers
```

## Required Jenkins Credentials

| ID | Type | Description |
|----|------|-------------|
| `aws-credentials` | AWS Credentials | IAM user Access Key + Secret |
| `rds-password` | Secret text | RDS master password |
| `ec2-ssh-key` | SSH Private Key | EC2 .pem key file |

## How Data Flows in Production

```
Browser → http://EC2_IP:3000
  → Nginx (frontend container)
    → /api/* → proxy_pass → Backend container :8080
      → Spring Boot → JDBC → RDS MySQL (private subnet)
    → /* → React SPA (index.html)
```

## Important Commands

```bash
# Local: start all 3 containers
docker compose up --build -d

# Local: stop everything
docker compose down -v

# Terraform: deploy infrastructure
cd terraform && terraform init && terraform apply

# Terraform: destroy everything (avoid charges!)
cd terraform && terraform destroy

# Push to ECR manually
aws ecr get-login-password --region ap-south-1 | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com
```
